thread.title: Home loans fall 6.1% in May

title: Home loans fall 6.1% in May
text:
Fri, Jul 10, 2015, 12:17 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 43 mins Home loans fall 6.1% in May AAP – 43 minutes ago Print 
Home loan approvals have fallen 6.1 per cent, disappointing economists' expectations of a 1.5 per cent fall. 
There were 50,366 approvals in May, compared to 53,643 approvals in April, the Australian Bureau of Statistics' seasonally adjusted figures show on Friday. 
The value of total housing finance fell 4.4 per cent in the month to $31.139 billion, with investor housing loans down 3.2 per cent and owner occupied housing down 5.3 per cent. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook PM backs Joyce despite anger over mine AAP
